terms.simple_intro3:
Welcome to the Haiti Mobility Dashboard developed by Flowminder. The platform provides access to authorised users to interactive visualisations of pre-computed and anonymised mobility indicators based on Digicel pseudonymised Call detail records and Flowminder Foundation's data processing methods.

The current version of the platform is a demonstration product. It shall not be used for any decision making or operational purposes (research included) without the express approval of the Flowminder Foundation (contact us at [haiti.mobility-dashboard@flowminder.org](mailto:haiti.mobility-dashboard@flowminder.org)).

The demonstration platform must be used only to visualise the mobility indicators provided. Without express written approval from the Flowminder Foundation, **the user shall not:**

1.  Download the data;
2.  Store the data;
3.  Manipulate data and create any product using the data;
4.  Using the data or any product derived from the data into publications;
5.  share the data with unauthorised user

Once your application has been approved, you will receive a copy terms in the Order From and the terms and conditions as described below.

tutorial.text5:
Data privacy and security is core to the collaboration between Flowminder and Digicel Haiti. For information on how data are collected, processed and protected, we recommend you read the following two pages:

1. Our [Website privacy notice](/privacy) describing how we protect the privacy of the visitors on this platform;

2. [Subscribers data privacy page](/subscriber-privacy), describing how we protect the privacy of Digicel Haiti's subscribers.
